cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.CC

The paper discusses two left-sequential logics for reasoning about propositional terms commonly used in programming languages. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of propositional terms, which could also place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also proposes evaluation trees as a natural semantics for the logics, which could place it in the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses connectives that prescribe different evaluation strategies, which could place it in the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
